Important Commands to Locate Files in Red Hat Linux
1️⃣ find – Search anywhere in filesystem
find /path -option value -print

Common usage:
Command	Explanation
find / -name httpd.conf	Find file by exact name
find /etc -type f	Find only files
find /var/log -type d	Find directories
find /home -size +100M	Find files >100MB
find /tmp -mtime -1	Modified within last 1 day
find / -user apache	Files owned by user
find / -perm 644	Files with permission 644
2️⃣ locate – Very fast file search

Uses a database /var/lib/mlocate/mlocate.db.

Commands:
locate filename


Example:

locate sshd_config


Update the database manually:

updatedb

3️⃣ which – Find the executable path
which ls


Output:

/usr/bin/ls

4️⃣ whereis – Show binary, source & man page
whereis bash


Example output:

bash: /usr/bin/bash /usr/share/man/man1/bash.1.gz

5️⃣ type – Shows how a command is interpreted
type cd
